South Africa ’s Competition Tribunal
said it received an application from three government
departments to postpone a hearing over Wal-Mart Stores Inc.’s
plan to take control of Johannesburg-based Massmart Holdings
Ltd. Business Report newspaper earlier reported that they may
oppose the transaction.  South Africa’s current account deficit narrowed to 2.7
percent of gross domestic product in the fourth quarter from 3
percent in the previous three months, according to the median
estimate of 19 economists surveyed by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
